header.gameNote: 2K SPORTS COACHES VS CANCER CLASSIC AT MEMPHIS TN

article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 66, Maine 62
article.story: MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) -- Lester Hudson scored 31 points, including two 3-pointers in the last minute, to help Tennessee-Martin beat Maine 66-62 on Tuesday in the consolation bracket of the 2K Sports College Hoops Classic. Hudson had 66 points for the Skyhawks (1-1) in the two-day Memphis regional of the tournament that benefits Coaches vs. Cancer. Gerald Robinson had 12 points and Joe Bailey added 11 for Tennessee-Martin, which took 33 of its 58 shots from 3-point range and finished at 27.3 percent from the beyond the arc. Brian Andre had 14 points and six rebounds, and Mark Socoby added nine points and 10 rebounds for the Black Bears (0-2), who shot 37.1 percent and turned the ball over 21 times. There were eight lead changes in the second half, but Tennessee-Martin hit late free throws to hold off Maine's full-court press. With the Skyhawks leading 59-57 and under a minute to play, Hudson connected twice from 3-point range to put the game out of reach. The Black Bears scored the game's first nine points, with Socoby hitting two 3-pointers during the stretch. Tennessee-Martin went on a 16-0 run to take a 25-22 lead, forcing Maine coach Ted Woodward to call two timeouts. The team's traded baskets and were tied 31-31 at halftime.
